    narr:generatedFrom "c354f003fe2a54a8d5d3268a64e6f8923cccb163" ;
    narr:narration """This hub collects style-metrics records for the full document corpus — register profiles, voice ratios, jargon density readings, and sentence-length patterns extracted from memos, call transcripts, design sessions, and engineering logs. The dominant signature across the corpus is what several nodes name explicitly: [the Scarlet session-memo idiolect](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_PractitionerBetaUserBarber_20260430) — antithesis-heavy structure, active voice dominant in editorial prose, short punchy declaratives at conviction peaks, and blockquoted speech that is run-on and filler-heavy. This pattern is attested from early March 2026 through mid-July, appearing in [strategic decision memos](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_CalibratedGrowth_20260527), [sales call notes](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_EnterpriseCustomerDemoCall_20260413), [correction memos](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_Correction_Tranche2_20260612), and [retrospective reflections](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_SessionReflection_20260416). Engineering and technical documents form a distinct register cluster: [post-mortem evaluations](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_ModelComparison_20260331) carry high RDF/SPARQL jargon density with no hedging in evaluative verdicts, while [infrastructure decision logs](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_N8nSQLiteToPostgres) are engineering-internal with imperative and declarative constructions. A third cluster covers voice-memo and transcript registers — [morning-pages style](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#StyleMetrics_Moonshot_20260701) with raw stream-of-consciousness blockquotes averaging ~35 words per sentence, contrasting sharply with the tighter editorial framing prose. The [voice-rule memo](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_ScarletVoiceRule_20260612) and [founding story](narr:https://aswritten.ai/narrative#Metrics_FoundingStory) mark the stylistic poles: one a short decision-memo with very low jargon density, the other high lexical diversity with technical embedding-space vocabulary.""" ;
